.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-env-download-symbols - Download AL symbol packages from a BC environment's dev endpoint


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock env download-symbols  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetch the symbol packages an AL project depends on from the connected BC
environment and write them to .alpackages/. Equivalent to VS Code's
"AL: Download symbols" - same wire protocol, no IDE required.

.PP
Reads app.json (default ./app.json) for:
  - "application" version  → Microsoft\fIApplication\fP\fI\&.app   (System + Base App combined)
  - "platform" version     → Microsoft\fISystem\fP\fP\&.app        (platform symbols)
  - "dependencies"         → one .app per entry            (per-tenant or 3rd-party deps)

.PP
Wire protocol (per Microsoft.Dynamics.Nav.Deployment.dll):
  GET {devEndpointUrl}dev/packages?publisher=&appName=&versionText=[&tenant=]
  Authorization: Basic base64(user:password)
  Accept: application/octet-stream, \fI/\fP
  → binary .app file in response body
(devEndpointUrl is {server}/{serverInstance}/ - launch.json-shaped - so we
append BC's dev-API path "dev/packages" to it.)

.PP
By default, packages already present in --out-dir are skipped (incremental).
Use --force to re-download.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error (download failed, env not running, no dev endpoint)
  3   auth failure (missing or invalid token)
  5   environment not found


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--app-json\fP="app.json"
	Path to the app.json driving symbol selection

.PP
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	Re-download even if a matching .app already exists in --out-dir

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for download-symbols

.PP
\fB--insecure\fP[=false]
	Skip TLS verification (use for self-signed local certs only)

.PP
\fB--out-dir\fP=".alpackages"
	Directory to write downloaded .app symbol packages into

.PP
\fB--tenant\fP="default"
	BC tenant the symbols belong to

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=5m0s
	Per-package download timeout


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock env download-symbols my-env
  bcdock env download-symbols my-env --app-json apps/MyExt/app.json --out-dir apps/MyExt/.alpackages
  bcdock env download-symbols my-env --force --tenant default
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-env(1)\fP
